Description: The Virgin seated in a landscape, suckling the Child on the flight into Egypt. Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Pier Francesco Mola
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (with Philipe's blindstamp and initials CMC)
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Jonathan Blackburne (on verso in pencil: "C.M.C.- 1765 / no. 56")
Acquisition notes: The inscription suggests that Cracherode had an earlier collection which he sold in 1765.
